ğŸ¦ XYZ Bank Branch Automation System
Core Java | OOP | MVC Architecture | Arrays | Abstract Classes

This project is an implementation of a Bank Branch Automation System based on a detailed case study provided for academic and learning purposes. The system simulates real-world banking operations using Core Java, applying Object-Oriented Programming, MVC architecture, and strict constraints including no use of public/private/protected for fields and methods except the main method.

ğŸš€ Features Implemented
ğŸ”¹ 1. Over-the-Counter (OTC) Banking Operations

Create new account

Deposit money

Withdraw money

Display specific account details

Show all accounts in the system

ğŸ”¹ 2. Account Types Implemented

Each type follows rules specified in the case study:

âœ” Savings Account

Minimum required balance: â‚¹10,000

Interest added monthly

âœ” Salary Account

Freezes automatically if no transactions occur for 2 months

Any new deposit unfreezes the account

Monthly interest added

âœ” Current Account

Overdraft facility

Minimal positive balance interest

No minimum balance restriction

âœ” Loan Account

Starts with negative balance (loan amount)

Deposits count as loan repayment

Monthly loan interest increases outstanding amount

No withdrawals allowed

ğŸ”¹ 3. Account Lifecycle Management

Account creation

Frozen-status handling (salary accounts)

Transaction validation and logging

ğŸ”¹ 4. Interest Calculation

Automatically applied monthly for all account types.

ğŸ”¹ 5. End-of-Day Transaction Report

Tracks all activities including deposits, withdrawals, interest updates, freezes, loan repayments, etc.

Prints a complete report with timestamps

Clears log after report generation

